F-flags raised in this batch (in F-1..F-49 Bucket A range per §13.2 + Bug #2):
  F-11 BRIEF_DRIFT — A4 brief conflated FA 2003 Sch 10 para 34 (overpayment-relief
    gateway) with the 4-year time limit. Correct architecture: para 34 (gateway) +
    para 34A (HMRC refusal grounds) + para 34B (4-year time limit). Corrected
    throughout A4 RUN output.
  F-12 BRIEF_DRIFT — A5 brief cited "FA 2003 Sch 9A para 11A (1-year UK-residence
    requalification refund)" for the non-UK resident surcharge refund. Correct
    cite verified at legislation.gov.uk: Sch 9A para 19 (verbatim: "may be
    amended, at any time before the end of the period of 2 years beginning with
    the day after the effective date of the transaction"). 2-year window, not
    1-year. Corrected throughout A5 RUN output and surfaced in worked Scenario B
    with explicit deadline computation.
  F-13 BRIEF_DRIFT — A6 brief and widely-circulated adviser commentary state
    Sch 4ZA para 16 inherited-interest carve-out as triple-condition (≤50% share +
    ≤£40k value + 3-year window). Verified verbatim at legislation.gov.uk: the
    statute has NO £40k value cap in paragraph 16. Two-condition only: (a) "P's
    beneficial share in the interest does not exceed 50%"; (b) "P is not to be
    treated... as having the major interest at any time during the period of three
    years beginning with the date of the inheritance". A6 RUN output corrects
    throughout, with an explicit "Note on the £40,000 question" paragraph
    addressing the widely-circulated misstatement and a four-scenario worked
    decision tree turning on the two correct conditions only.
  F-14 EXISTING_PAGE_STALE — Existing site page sdlt-on-probate-property-transfers
    cites "Paragraph 8 Schedule 4 FA 2003" for the deed-of-variation exemption.
    Verified verbatim at legislation.gov.uk: the substantive DoV exemption is at
    FA 2003 Sch 3 para 4 (the no-charge-on-relevant-transactions schedule), with
    Sch 4 para 8A providing a parallel chargeable-consideration carve-out where
    the Sch 3 para 4 condition is failed through containing consideration. The
    existing page should be back-patched at FAQ #2 + the five-transfer-type table
    row + the Deeds of Variation H2 to cite "Sch 3 para 4 (gateway) with Sch 4
    para 8A (carve-out)". Wave-close cleanup; non-blocking for RUN continuation.

